BAPE’s signature ABC camo print is outlined in white on the black canvas upper, fortified with tonal suede construction on the forefoot and heel overlay. Molded white side stripes adorn an upper built with a combination of black canvas, leather and suede. ‘Mastermind Japan’ is embroidered on the toe box, while the brand’s skull and crossbones graphic appears on the medial eyestay and lateral heel. The sneaker rides on a black rubber midsole, featuring a contrasting white toe bumper and ‘Mastermind’ etched in block lettering on the lateral sidewall. results.name: END. x Mastermind Japan x Old Skool 'White'
results.story: The END. x Mastermind Japan x Vans Old Skool ‘White’ brings Masaaki Homma’s meticulous vision and rebellious attitude to the vintage skate shoe. A one-note ivory finish is executed on the upper, built with a traditional bend of canvas, leather and suede. The sneaker’s side stripes are molded and raised, while the low-cut collar is unfinished, leaving the interior foam padding exposed. Additional details include doubled-up tongues and Vans’ checkerboard print on the medial side panel. Anchoring the low-top is an off-white rubber midsole with ‘Mastermind’ stamped in block lettering on the lateral sidewall. Underfoot, a black and white checkerboard pattern is revealed beneath the translucent rubber outsole.

results.name: Supreme x Half Cab 'Barbed Wire - White'
results.story: Made exclusively for the New York skate brand, the Supreme x Vans Half Cab ‘Barbed Wire’ adds a graphic element to a two-tone colorway of the classic skate shoe. The upper is constructed from off-white suede with contrasting black accents on the laces, padded tongue, and woven Half Cab labels. The sneaker is mounted on a black vulcanized rubber midsole, accented with a white barbed wire graphic and a crimson Supreme-branded license plate at the heel.

results.name: Supreme x Old Skool 'Barbed Wire - Royal'
results.story: The Supreme x Vans Old Skool ‘Barbed Wire’ delivers the New York skate brand’s take on the vintage silhouette that debuted in 1977 as the Vans #36. The low-top features a royal blue canvas upper with charcoal suede overlays and a color-matched leather side stripe. A dual-branded tag adorns the interior tongue, while a Supreme wordmark is debossed on the heel overlay. The sneaker sits atop a white vulcanized rubber midsole, accented with a wraparound barbed wire graphic and a red license plate at the heel.

results.name: Vans Vault Sk8-Hi Cap LX MASTERMIND World Marshmallow

A monochrome off-white is applied to the mixed material build, highlighted by an asymmetrical blend of leather, canvas and suede. The lateral side features zip closure, an elongated eyestay, and a leather side stripe with exposed zigzag stitching. A perforated side stripe accompanies Mastermind’s signature skull and crossbones graphic on the medial side. The high-top is mounted on a deconstructed midsole, featuring exaggerated proportions and misaligned details. Underfoot, Vans’ signature checkerboard print enlivens the translucent rubber outsole.

A traditional Vans tag hangs off the lateral eyestay, while a Supreme wordmark is debossed on the heel overlay. The sneaker rides on a white vulcanized rubber midsole, featuring a wraparound barbed wire graphic, a black foxing stripe, and a red Supreme-branded license plate.

results.name: END. x Mastermind Japan x Sk8-Hi 'Black'

A white barbed wire graphic garlands the black vulcanized rubber midsole, supported underfoot by a waffle-traction gum rubber outsole. A red Supreme-branded license plate provides a solitary pop of color.

Black leather lines the interior, while a PopCush insole provides lightweight cushioning. A black barbed wire graphic wraps around the white rubber midsole, accented with a red Supreme-branded license plate at the heel.

results.story: The Nigel Cabourn x Vans OG Classic Slip-On LX ‘Carpet Green Mix’ features a unique design inspired by a vintage chair that the British designer discovered during one of his trips to California. results.name: Nigel Cabourn x OG Classic Slip-On LX 'USMC Army Mix'
results.story: Taken from a capsule collection with the British menswear designer, the Nigel Cabourn x Vans OG Classic Slip-On LX ‘USMC Army Mix’ applies varying shades of green to an upper built with cotton and herringbone — the same materials used to manufacture US Army uniforms in the late 1930s. Details include rip-and-repair stitching and branded eyelets inspired by drainage ports used in US military boots. The sneaker is mounted on an olive drab vulcanized rubber midsole with tonal license plate branding and a tan foxing stripe.

results.name: Vans Vault OG Authentic LX Nigel Cabourn Army Camo
results.story: Dropping as part of an apparel and footwear collection with the British menswear designer, the Nigel Cabourn x Vans OG Authentic LX ‘Army Green Camo’ draws inspiration from a WW2 USMC HBT shirt. A green and red camo pattern suffuses the aged cotton canvas upper, featuring branded eyelets and rip-and-repair stitching. Cabourn’s signature broad arrow is embroidered on the tongue, while his name is emblazoned on the sockliner. The lace-up rides on a vulcanized rubber midsole, underpinned by Vans’ waffle-traction outsole in sticky gum rubber.

results.name: Vans Vault OG Authentic LX Nigel Cabourn Navy Mix
results.story: The Nigel Cabourn x Vans OG Authentic LX ‘Crazy Navy Mix’ delivers the British menswear designer’s color-blocked interpretation of the classic lace-up. Inspired by vintage US naval workwear, the sneaker features an aged canvas build with dark navy paneling on the forefoot, vibrant indigo on the lateral side panel, neutral grey on the medial side, and a bright red heel strip outlined in contrasting black stitching. An embroidered broad arrow decorates the tongue, while Nigel Cabourn branding is embossed on the sneaker’s eyelets. Underfoot, a waffle-tread gum rubber outsole offers grippy traction.

results.name: Vans OG Style 24 LX Nigel Cabourn Denim
results.story: Drawn from a capsule collection with the British menswear designer, the Nigel Cabourn x Vans OG Style 24 LX High ‘Denim’ showcases a dark navy finish on a mixed-material build. The sneaker’s tongue and lateral side are constructed from cotton canvas, while the medial side panel is rendered in herringbone twill. Details include branded eyelets, a white rubber toe cap and a red embroidered arrow atop the tongue. The high-top rests on a solid white rubber midsole, reinforced underfoot by a waffle-traction gum rubber outsole.

results.name: Vans Vault OG Authentic LX Nigel Cabourn Natural Navy
results.story: Releasing as part of a capsule collection with the British designer, the Nigel Cabourn x Vans OG Authentic LX ‘USN’ takes inspiration from US Naval deck plimsolls from the Second World War. The low-top makes use of a tan cotton canvas upper with rip-and-repair stitching and branded eyelets. Cabourn’s embroidered broad arrow decorates the tongue, while ‘USN’ is stenciled on each toe box. The sneaker rests on a navy vulcanized rubber midsole with a contrasting red foxing stripe.

results.name: Nigel Cabourn x OG Style 24 LX 'Navy Ventile'
results.story: Releasing as part of an expansive collection with the British menswear designer, the Nigel Cabourn x Vans OG Style 24 LX ‘Navy Ventile’ showcases a monochrome palette on a low-top edition of a vintage skate shoe originally released in the ‘80s. The upper is crafted from water-resistant navy cotton Ventile with a tonal rubber toe cap and branded eyelets. Contrasting scarlet accents appear on an embroidered arrow atop the tongue and dual pinstripe detailing on the navy rubber midsole.
